    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const rawAuthor = $json.author;\nconst author =\n  typeof rawAuthor === 'string'\n    ? rawAuthor\n    : rawAuthor?.username || rawAuthor?.name || '';\n\nconst mrTitle = $json.mr_title || '';\nconst source = $json.source_branch || '';\nconst target = $json.target_branch || '';\nconst changes = JSON.stringify($json.changes || []).slice(0, 12000);\n\nconst prompt = `\nYou are a strict senior code reviewer for a web game platform.\n\nProject context:\n- Frontend: Phaser-based web game client\n- Backend: Spring Boot 4 API server\n- Authentication and authorization are managed by Keycloak\n- Merge request diffs may include frontend, backend, or both\n\nYour task:\nReview the merge request changes and return ONLY valid UTF-8 JSON.\nDo not include markdown fences, prose outside JSON, or any extra keys.\n\nReturn a JSON object with exactly these keys:\nmr_type, summary, overall_risk, findings, comment_markdown\n\nRules:\n- mr_type must be one of: fix, feat, docs, refactor, test, chore\n- overall_risk must be one of: low, medium, high\n- findings must be an array\n- each finding must contain exactly these keys: severity, file, line_hint, issue, suggestion\n- severity must be one of: high, medium, low\n- All human-readable text values must be written in Korean\n- summary must be Korean\n- findings.issue must be Korean\n- findings.suggestion must be Korean\n- comment_markdown must be Korean\n\nReview priorities:\n1. Bug risk and behavioral regression\n2. Security issues, especially auth/authz, token handling, trust boundaries, insecure defaults\n3. Runtime stability, null handling, exception flow, async issues\n4. Performance or resource waste\n5. Maintainability and readability\n\nFrontend review guidance:\n- Check Phaser scene lifecycle, scene transitions, duplicate event listeners, cleanup leaks, asset loading risks\n- Check async API handling, race conditions, stale state, browser-side auth assumptions, broken redirects or callback handling\n- Check whether UI code can break on missing API fields or partial responses\n\nBackend review guidance:\n- Check Spring Boot 4 controller, service, config, and security changes for regressions\n- Check request validation, exception handling, null safety, startup risks, and operational assumptions\n- Assume Keycloak manages tokens, so focus on whether the application validates and uses identity safely\n- Flag risky public endpoint exposure, incorrect trust of headers or client state, and fragile environment assumptions\n\nClassification guidance:\n- Use feat for new user-facing capability\n- Use fix for bug fixes\n- Use refactor for structural changes without intended behavior change\n- Use docs for documentation-only changes\n- Use test for test-only changes\n- Use chore for maintenance or mixed changes that do not fit better\n\nOutput requirements:\n- Keep summary concise, 1 to 3 sentences\n- findings should include only meaningful issues, not trivial style comments\n- If no important issues are found, findings must be []\n- comment_markdown must be a concise Korean GitLab MR review comment\n- comment_markdown should include a short overall assessment, risk level, key findings if any, and a brief conclusion\n\nInput:\n- MR title: ${mrTitle}\n- Author: ${author}\n- Branches: ${source} -> ${target}\n- Changes JSON: ${changes}\n`;\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    ...$json,\n    prompt\n  }\n};"
      },
